description: This unit process represents the combustion of natural gas. The data scope is gate-to-grave, encompassing the combustion of fuel in the specified equipment. The data was developed from NETL datasets, which incorporate Webfire circa 2014 as the primry source of emissions factors.

exchanges.description: Dichloromethane (methylene chloride) [Halogenated organic emissions to air]

processDocumentation.dataCollectionDescription: Emissions data were collected from the EPA WebFIRE database.
processDocumentation.dataSelectionDescription: NETL calculates combustion emissions based on the data reported in the EPA WebFIRE database. WebFIRE is the EPA's online database that contains emissions factors for criteria and hazardous air pollutants (HAP) for industrial and non-industrial processes and multiple reports submitted to the EPA using the Compliance and Emissions Data Reporting Interface (CEDRI) in response to regulatory requirements under Parts 60 and 63 of Title 40 of the U.S. Code of Federal Regulations (CFR).
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: NETL calculates combustion emissions based on the data reported in the EPA WebFIRE database.The database was filtered down to the intended fuel and equipment type, and emissions were normalized to the basis of 1 kg fuel combusted.
processDocumentation.intendedApplication: This unit process is intended as a stand-alone gate-to-gate representation of Natural Gas combustion in industrial boilers or internal combustion engines. It may be applied as a generic data source in other models.
processDocumentation.projectDescription: This unit process includes the emissions associated with the combustion of natural gas.
